Package: mteucb
Title: Marginal Treatment Effect
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
     c(person("Toshiki", "Tsuda", email="tsuda.toshiki.r73@kyoto-u.jp", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
     person("Jin", "Yanchun", email="chnjyc@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cph")),
     person("Ryo", "Okui", email="okuiryo@e.u-tokyo.ac.jp", role = c("aut", "cph")))
Description: This package cmputes  uniform confidence bands for the MTE function proposed in Tsuda, T, Jin, Y., & Okui, R. (2024+). A uniform confidence band covers the true function with a prespecified probability. These bands are used to make statistical inferences on the shape of the MTE function. Uniform confidence bands are particularly useful because they can visualize the statistical uncertainty behind the estimated MTE function.
